@startuml Activity Diagram - Scan Pipeline
!theme cerulean-outline

title SmartMedia - Activity Diagram (Media Scanning & Processing Pipeline)

start
:📂 **START**: User selects folder;
:🔍 **Get Folder Path**;

:🔎 Traverse Directory Recursively;
note right: Walk through all subdirectories
:📋 Get file list;

while (More files?) is (Yes)
  :📄 Read next file;
  :📝 Get file extension;
  
  if (Is Image/Video/Audio?) is (No)
    :⏭️  Skip file;
    note right: Not a supported media type
  else (Yes)
    :🔢 Compute MD5 hash;
    note right: Used as unique ID
    
    if (Already in DB?) is (Yes)
      :🔗 Link to existing record;
      note right: File already scanned
    else (No)
      
      :📐 Get file metadata;
      :📊 Extract: size, modified_date;
      
      if (Media Type?) is (Image)
        :🖼️  Resize image;
        note right: MAX_IMAGE_SIZE = 256px
        
        :🧠 Load Qwen2-VL Model;
        note right: GPU-accelerated inference
        
        :🔄 Generate Prompt;
        note right: Optimized for fast response
        :⚡ Run Inference;
        note right: max_new_tokens = 85
        :🎨 Extract metadata;
        note right: caption, emotion, objects
        
        :👁️  Detect Faces;
        note right: HOG detector (fast)
        :📦 Generate Face Encodings;
        note right: 128-dim vectors
        
        :📐 Check for EXIF data;
        if (Has GPS?) is (Yes)
          :🗺️  Extract coordinates;
          :🌍 Reverse geocode;
          note right: Optional: call OSM API
        else (No)
        endif
        
        :🖼️  Generate Thumbnail;
        note right: Resize to 400x400
        :💾 Save to disk;
        
      else if (Media Type?) is (Video)
        :🎥 Extract duration;
        note right: Use OpenCV
        :🎬 Extract frame @ 10%;
        note right: Create thumbnail image
        :🖼️  Generate Thumbnail;
        :💾 Save to disk;
        :✅ Mark as video;
        
      else if (Media Type?) is (Audio)
        :🎵 Extract duration;
        note right: Read audio metadata
        :🎨 Create gradient thumbnail;
        note right: Pink-orange gradient
        :💾 Save to disk;
        :✅ Mark as audio;
        
      endif
      
      :📊 Generate Embedding;
      note right: Sentence-Transformers (1536-dim)
      
      :💾 **Save to Database**;
      note right
        INSERT or REPLACE:
        • id, path, filename
        • caption, emotion, objects
        • metadata (JSON)
        • face_count
        • thumbnail_path
        • media_type
        • duration (if video/audio)
      end note
      
      :📑 **Add to FAISS Index**;
      note right: For semantic search
      
      :📤 **Send Progress Update**;
      note right: IPC to UI with:
      • current file count
      • filename
      • detected_faces
      • generated_caption
      
    endif
    
  endif
  
endwhile (No)

:✅ **Processing Complete**;
:📊 Update Library Statistics;
note right
  • Total media count
  • Faces count
  • Processing time
  • Storage used
end note

:🎉 **Scan Finished**;
note right: User notified via UI
:Show summary;
:Offer background processing;
stop

---

partition "Error Handling" {
  if (File read error?) is (Yes)
    :⚠️  Log error;
    :⏭️  Skip and continue;
  else (No)
  endif
  
  if (AI inference error?) is (Yes)
    :⚠️  Log error;
    :📝 Use fallback: filename only;
  else (No)
  endif
  
  if (Database error?) is (Yes)
    :❌ Rollback transaction;
    :🔔 Notify user;
  else (No)
  endif
}

---

note bottom
  **Performance Metrics:**
  • File traversal: O(n) files
  • Image processing: ~2 sec/image (GPU)
  • Video thumbnail: ~0.5 sec
  • Audio metadata: ~0.05 sec
  • Database write: ~5ms
  • Total: ~n*2 sec for n images
  
  **Optimization Strategies:**
  ✓ Batch processing (vectorized inference)
  ✓ GPU acceleration (CUDA)
  ✓ Caching (skip already scanned)
  ✓ Background processing (non-blocking)
  ✓ Token reduction (85 vs 140)
end note

@enduml
